## [SECTION 5 — 5:30 to 6:30] Intentional rejections — error messages are good

*[Screen: red ERROR lines appear in the terminal — things like `Guest("Study is at capacity")`]*

> "You'll see red error messages appearing. I want to be clear about what these are — they're not failures. They're the system correctly rejecting invalid inputs.
>
> That one says 'Study is at capacity' — we're testing that a third validator can't claim a study that already has its full panel. The test passes because the rejection happened correctly.
>
> Other tests in this section are checking that a validator from the same institution as the researcher is blocked — that's the conflict of interest check — and that a validator can't submit two attestations for the same study. Each red line is a guard working."

