## [SECTION 6 — 6:30 to 8:00] End to end — a Harmony Record appears

*[Screen: `3. Full end-to-end round > researcher → request → validator attestations → HarmonyRecord on public DHT`]*

> "This test runs the complete sequence from submission to outcome. A researcher submits a study to the network. Validators claim it, do their work, commit their assessments, and reveal them. The governance network then assembles a Harmony Record on the public distributed hash table.
>
> A Harmony Record is the permanent output of a ValiChord round. It records what validators found, how much they agreed, who participated, and how long it took. It's immutable — the validation rules in the Rust code reject any attempt to update or delete it. It lives on the public network where journals, funders, and anyone else can read it without running a Holochain node.
>
> This test proves that chain works, end to end, across real nodes."

