## Recording notes

- **Pause** before Section 4 — the commit-reveal explanation is the most important part. Don't rush it.
- **The gaps** where nothing is happening on screen (conductors starting) are where the narration carries the weight. That's intentional — the slowness is real Holochain nodes doing real work.
- **The red error lines** — mention them before they appear, not after. Viewers who see red and hear silence will assume something went wrong.
- **Keep the font large.** The test names are the only thing a non-technical viewer can anchor on — they need to be readable.
